In Japan, [[Morinaga]] has been selling &quot;angel pie&quot;, a marshmallow version of chocopie since 1958[http://www.morinaga.co.jp/angelpie/history.html]. So it is not an invention of Orion. In addition, チョコパイ (chocopie in Japanese) is trademarked by two different companies, Lotte and Furuta as &quot;ロッテチョコパイ&quot;(Lotte chocopie) and &quot;フルタチョコパイ&quot;(Furuta chocopie). Chocopie itself is not trademarked, ... probably because it is considered as a common noun.--[[User:Mochi|Mochi]] ([[User talk:Mochi|talk]]) 12:11, 26 February 2011 (UTC)

